**The shifting conversation.** Google's Cloud Next conference wrapped last week. The biggest takeaway: the corporate conversation is quickly shifting from "Can we build an agent?" to "How do we manage thousands of them?" — and the search giant announced several new tools to make it possible.

**Enterprise Agents.** The new [Gemini Enterprise Agent Platform](https://cloud.google.com/blog/products/ai-machine-learning/introducing-gemini-enterprise-agent-platform) is Alphabet’s new platform to build, scale, and optimize fleets of agents. Use the no-code Agent Designer to build custom agents, or pull pre-built templates from the Cloud Marketplace. The platform supports 200+ leading models, including third-party options. 

**Workspace Intelligence**. [Workspace Intelligence](https://workspace.google.com/blog/product-announcements/introducing-workspace-intelligence) bridges context between Gmail, Docs, Sheets, Slides, and Drive, turning all your files into a cohesive knowledge graph. Ask Gemini_ _in Chat is the new way to run this intelligence: just state your goal in Google Chat, and Gemini works behind the scenes to deliver the final product. See what else is new across Sheets, Docs, and Slides [here](https://workspace.google.com/blog/product-announcements/introducing-workspace-intelligence#:~:text=Go%20from%20blank%20page%20to%20brilliance%20in%20Sheets%2C%20Docs%2C%20and%20Slides).

**The Apple overhaul. **Cloud CEO Thomas Kurian reminded everyone that Apple's upcoming [Siri overhaul](https://9to5mac.com/2026/04/22/google-teases-gemini-powered-siri-upgrade-during-cloud-next-keynote/) will be powered by Gemini. The overhaul is expected to include a standalone Siri app, persistent chat logs, and a more traditional chatbot experience.

**Other updates worth knowing. **The company also rolled out two new 8th-gen tensor processing units: TPU 8t for training and TPU 8i for inference. Learn all 260 announcements from the conference [here](https://cloud.google.com/blog/topics/google-cloud-next/google-cloud-next-2026-wrap-up).


